wdi2-SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD.def: Current private expenditures on health per capita expressed in current US dollars. Domestic private sources include funds from households, corporations and non-profit organizations. Such expenditures can be either prepaid to voluntary health insurance or paid directly to healthcare providers.
wdi2-SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD.name: Domestic private health expenditure per capita
wdi2-SH.XPD.PVTD.PC.CD.source: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database).
